headline: Goldman Sachs Agri Stock Picks: Corteva's R&D Edge, FMC's Pipeline, And Mosaic's Phosphate Advantage Set Up Strong Growth
summary: Goldman Sachs analyst Duffy Fischer initiated coverage on several major U.S. agriculture input stocks, citing several factors. The analyst writes that they believe the agricultural macro environment is still stabilizing after the peak caused by the Russia-Ukraine war. Fischer says that while Spring 2025 looks better than expected (excluding FX) thanks to expected higher corn acreage and a short Fall application window, they anticipate a continued drift toward normalized levels later this year. C

headline: Potash miner K+S says US farmers to foot the bill for Trump's tariffs
summary: Germany's K+S, whichexports potash to U.S. farmers from Canada, on Thursday said itwould pass any tariff-related costs onto customers, after its2025 earnings forecast disappointed investors. ...
